<p class="text">We've given this month's Compass competition a slightly different slant. For a chance to win one of 20 Lonely Planet guidebooks (we'll be sending winners a voucher), we'd like you to tell us what country you would be in if you asked the question "ta-pai-ko bi-hah bha-yo?" (that's a transliteration of the script), and what would you be asking? Small hint - the language isn't Hindi but it's a close relation.</p>

              <p class="text">We're continuing with an added bonus for ekno members. Send your entry to us via your ekno email address and if you're lucky enough to be one of the 20 book winners your luck might hold and you might be one of the four people who win a US$20 account top-up. What on earth is ekno, you might ask? Find out more at:<a href="http://www.ekno.lonelyplanet.com" target="_blank"> 
                http://www.ekno.lonelyplanet.com</a></p>

<p class="text">Last month the answer we wanted was Marin County, California, USA. The lucky winners, each of whom will be receiving a book voucher, are:<br>

Alison Byrne, Amanda Buster, Andra Howman, Anja Feickert, Catherine Donohoe, Chris Miller, Daren Fawkes, Dave Machenry, Gavin Kean, Jason Blackman, Joan Calladine, Jorge Torterolo, Kate Parmenter, Katherine Westfall, Megan Campbell, Natasha Krochina, Steve Barber, Tom Toberty, Vicky Caveliers and Walter Wood.</p>

